.TH "CSSGROUPINGRULE.INSERTRULE" "3JS" "November 7, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
CSSGroupingRule.insertRule \- CSSGroupingRule: insertRule() method
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]insertRule()\f[B]\f[R] method of the
\f[CR]CSSGroupingRule\f[R] interface adds a new CSS rule to a list of
CSS rules.
.SH SYNTAX
.IP
.EX
insertRule(rule)
insertRule(rule, index)
.EE
.SS Parameters
.TP
\f[B]rule\f[R]
A string
.TP
\f[B]index\f[R] \f[I](optional)\f[R]
An optional index at which to insert the rule; defaults to 0.
.SS Return value
The index of the new rule.
.SS Exceptions
.TP
\f[B]IndexSizeError\f[R] \f[B]DOMException\f[R]
Thrown if \f[I]index\f[R] is greater than the number of child CSS rules.
.TP
\f[B]HierarchyRequestError\f[R] \f[B]DOMException\f[R]
Thrown if \f[CR]rule\f[R] cannot be inserted at the specified index due
to some CSS constraint.
.TP
\f[B]HierarchyRequestError\f[R] \f[B]DOMException\f[R]
Thrown if the \f[CR]rule\f[R] is a valid statement but not a nested
statement.
.SH EXAMPLES
.IP
.EX
\f[B]let\f[R] myRules = document.styleSheets[0].cssRules;
myRules[0].insertRule(
  \(dqhtml {background\-color: blue;}\(dq,
  0,
); \f[I]/* inserts a rule for the HTML element at position 0 */\f[R]
.EE
